HEADWORD: Conifer
<hw>Co"ni*fer</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>conifer</ets>; <ets>conus</ets> cone + <ets>ferre</ets> to bear:
cf. F. <ets>conif⟦egrave⟧re</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A tree
or shrub bearing cones; one of the order <ord>Coniferae</ord>, which
includes the pine, cypress, and (according to some) the yew.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

